<DOC><DOCNO> AP880701-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-01-88 0125EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Brazil-Gambling     07-01 0078</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Brazil-Gambling,0081</SECOND><HEAD>Brazil Congress Says No To Casinos</HEAD><DATELINE>BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Congress has rejected aconstitutional amendment to bring back casino gambling to LatinAmerica's largest nation.   The vote, on Thursday, was 271-118 in favor, with 14abstentions, but it fell nine short of the majority needed to passa constitutional amendment.   Casinos were outlawed in Brazil by presidential decree in 1946.   The Congress is sitting as a constitutional convention torewrite Brazil's military-dictated constitution.</TEXT></DOC>